title: COLLEGE ROUNDUP: Scranton field hockey clinches berth in Landmark Conference tourney
text:
Sign Up Text Alerts | newsletter 
Hat tricks power Royals to rout 
Alyssa Whitman and Krista Osborne each notched hat tricks to help the University of Scranton’s field hockey team roll to a 9-2 victory over Moravian College and secure a spot in the upcoming Landmark Conference Tournament. 
Jessica Pankey added two goals and Ana Bisciello scored the other for the Royals, who built a 4-2 halftime lead.
